Yes, I suppose deep inside I know it must be done Kezzek, I suppose I am just trying to hold on to how the Safehouse once was. It has changed much. But yes there is much more volume nowadays, and I admit I rarely browse the Main Lounge now, and I don't visit the Training Studio to bestow knowledge as much as I ought to considering how much I gleaned there. It seems we have passed the bounds of what was at one time simply a "family." I do miss those times, and I think that's why I find myself mostly in the Root Celler and The Arena now -- because those are the people I am closest with, in-game or just from within the Safehouse. There was once a time when I'd click on a forum, and over 75% of the names of the posters I'd recognize, could probably tell you about what level they were, what server they were on, what their sig was, and chances are what guild they were in. I now open one and I recognize maybe at most 10%, and even those I know little about unless they play on Rallos or have been around for half a year or so.<br>
