- I know Ozaak wasn't banned and just simply left.  The question is, though, why did he leave?  He was driven away after a - and I have to admit, a somewhat uncalled for - flame of his. <br>
<br>
- I certainly don't think that you ban people because of who they are.  I know you better than that.  Yes, you ban people because they cannot stick to rules.  What I am suggesting is that the rules need to be changed and relaxed somewhat.<br>
<br>
- The rules, as they are now, are driving some exceptional people away.  I don't think that benefits the Safehouse.<br>
<br>
- Even with a more relaxed set of rules, I am sure the mods will have their hands full.<br>
